{{italic title}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} [[File:From_Language_to_Language_poster.jpeg|thumb|Film poster]] '''''From Language to Language''''' (Hebrew: '''משפה לשפה''', tr. ''MiSafa LeSafa'') is a 55-minute 2004 Belgian-French-German-Israeli Hebrew-language independent underground experimental documentary art film directed by [[Nurith Aviv]].
==Synopsis== The film, produced by {{ill|Marek Rozenbaum|he|מרק רוזנבאום|pl}} and the [[Dardenne brothers]], was released on DVD by {{ill|Éditions Montparnasse|fr}} as part of a boxset also including 2008’s ''[[Langue sacrée, langue parlée]]'' and 2011’s ''[[Traduire]]'',<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.editionsmontparnasse.fr/p1358/Nurith-Aviv-Coffret-DVD|people=Aviv, Nurith|title=''Nurith Aviv (Coffret 3 DVD)''|location=Paris|publisher=Éditions Montparnasse|language=French|accessdate=4 March 2018|format=DVD|oclc=650587091|date=18 May 2011|id=3346030022979|trans-title=''Nurith Aviv (3 DVD Boxset)''}}</ref> with which they form a trilogy.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bar-On|first=Yaakov|date=19 December 2016|script-title=he:נשארת בתמונה|trans-title=She Stays in the Picture|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/cerveau/article_presse/MAARIV_2016.pdf|language=Hebrew|work=[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=28 April 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''[[The Jerusalem Post]]''|pages=10–11}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=8 July 2011|script-title=Rendering a Reborn Tongue|last=Katz|first=Lisa|url=https://www.haaretz.com/1.372135|work=[[Haaretz]]|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=[[M. DuMont Schauberg]] and {{ill|Haaretz Group (Company)|ar|مجموعة هاآرتس|de|Haaretz-Gruppe|he|קבוצת הארץ|lt=Haaretz Group}}|access-date=23 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=1 February 2011|script-title=''Traduire'' – Review|last=Mandelbaum|first=Jacques|author-link=Jacques Mandelbaum|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/feb/01/nurith-aviv-film-language-review|work=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|access-date=23 April 2018}}</ref> It contains interviews with Israeli artists and writers such as [[Aharon Appelfeld]], [[Evgenia Dodina]], [[Salman Masalha]], [[Agi Mishol]], [[Amal Murkus]], Prof. Dr. {{ill|Haviva Pedaya|he|חביבה פדיה}}, [[Haïm Ulliel]], and [[Meir Wieseltier]] who write in Hebrew even though it is not their native language about the importance of language and asks how the struggle between their mother tongue and Hebrew has affected their art.<ref>{{ill|Yudilovitch, Merav|he|מרב יודילוביץ'}}. {{cite news|date=26 September 2008|script-title=he:ניצחון ההולכים נגד הזרם|trans-title=The Victory of Those Who Go Against the Stream|url=https://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-3601999,00.html|language=Hebrew|work=[[Yedioth Ahronoth]]''’s'' ''[[Ynet]]''|location=Rishon LeZion|access-date=4 March 2018|publisher=Yedioth Ahronoth Group}}</ref><ref>{{ill|Anderman, Nirit|he|נירית אנדרמן}}. {{cite news|date=3 February 2012|script-title=he:לדבר קולנועית: ראיון עם הבמאית והצלמת נורית אביב|trans-title=Speaking Film: Interview With Director and Cinematographer Nurith Aviv|url=http://haaretz.co.il/1.1632553|language=Hebrew|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=4 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=2 April 2004|script-title=he:רק השפה העברית היא מולדת|trans-title=Only Hebrew Is a Motherland|last=Gur|first=Batya|author-link=Batya Gur|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/misafa/BatiaGour|language=Hebrew|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=4 March 2018|page=113}}</ref><ref>Raizen, Prof. Dr. Esther. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/23062661 ''From Language to Language'']. In: ''Middle East Studies Association Bulletin'', Tucson, Arizona: [[Middle East Studies Association of North America]], Volume 40, Number 1, June 2006, pp. 127–129. Retrieved 24 March 2018.</ref><ref>{{ill|Golan, Dr. Ruth|he|רות גולן}}. שפת האם, שפת האב, השפה הטפילית והשפה הארוטית: על סרטה של נורית אביב '''משפה לשפה''' [Mother Tongue, Father’s Language, Parasitic Language, and Erotic Language: On Nurith Aviv’s Film ''From Language to Language'']. In: {{cite book|date=2007|script-title=he:'''דוקומנטלי: אסופת מאמרים על קולנוע דוקומנטרי ישראלי'''|trans-title=Documentally: Essays on Israeli Documentary Cinema|pages=230–235|location=Te