==Reception== Between its release and 2006, the film was screened and won several awards at [[Docaviv|DocAviv]], [[Marseille Festival of Documentary Film]], [[Visions du Réel]], [[Internationales Dokumentarfilmfestival München]], [[Musée d'Art et d'Histoire du Judaïsme|Musée d’Art et d’Histoire du Judaïsme]], {{ill|Les 3 Luxembourg|fr}}, {{ill|Espace analytique|fr}}, {{ill|États généraux du film documentaire|fr}}, [[Centre culturel international de Cerisy-la-Salle]], {{ill|Israel Psychoanalytic Society|he|החברה הפסיכואנליטית בישראל}}, [[Strasbourg Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art]], [[Martin-Gropius-Bau]], [[University of Lausanne]], and many other places.<ref>{{cite news|last=Yudilovitch|first=Merav|date=30 March 2004|script-title=he:הזוכה בפסטיבל ״דוקאביב:״ '''משפה לשפה'''|trans-title=The Winner at DocAviv: ''From Language to Language''|url=https://www.ynet.co.il/articles/1,7340,L-2896554,00.html|language=Hebrew|work=Yedioth Ahronoth''’s'' ''Ynet''|location=Rishon LeZion|access-date=26 March 2018|publisher=Yedioth Ahronoth Group}}</ref><ref>{{ill|Schnitzer, Meir|he|מאיר שניצר}}. {{cite news|date=31 March 2004|script-title=he:קלוז־אפ על השונה|trans-title=Closeup on Difference|url=http://www.makorrishon.co.il/nrg/online/archive/ART/680/382.html|language=Hebrew|work=Maariv|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=26 March 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''The Jerusalem Post''}}</ref><ref>{{ill|Pinto, Goel|he|גואל פינטו}}. {{cite news|date=31 March 2004|script-title=DocAviv Prize Goes to Film About Struggling With Hebrew|url=http://haaretz.com/1.4769968|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=4 March 2018}} Hebrew original: {{cite news|last=Pinto|first=Goel|date=30 March 2004|script-title=he:בין שפת התמונות לשפת המלים||trans-title=Between the Language of the Images and the Language of the Words|url=http://haaretz.co.il/1.955929|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=6 October 2018}}</ref> The film was produced by [[ZDF]], [[Arte]], {{ill|Noga Communications|he|נגה תקשורת}}, {{ill|New Fund for Cinema and Television|he|הקרן החדשה לקולנוע וטלוויזיה}}, and {{ill|Israel’s Channel 8|he|ערוץ 8}}. It was also screened at [[Centre Georges Pompidou]] in 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last=Esterkin|first=Jonathan|script-title=he:שפת המוח|trans-title=Language of the Brain|date=15 May 2016|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/cerveau/article_presse/maariv1505.jpg|language=Hebrew|work=Maariv|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=28 April 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''The Jerusalem Post''}}</ref>
