{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 528 |organ = SC |date = 21 December |year = 1982 |meeting = 2,410 |code = S/RES/528 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/528(1982) |for = |abstention = |against = |subject = Working languages of the Security-Council |result = Adopted |image = Arabic Language.svg |caption = Arabic }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[United Nations Security Council resolution|Security Council Resolution]] 528''', adopted on December 21, 1982, after the [[United Nations General Assembly|General Assembly]] passed [[United Nations General Assembly Resolution 3190|Resolution 3190]] extolling the virtues of expanded working languages, the Council decided to include [[Arabic language|Arabic]] among the working languages of the Security Council.
No details of the voting were given, other than that it was adopted "by consensus".
